The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	Kolar, May 18 (PTI): Twenty-one people have died in poll-bound Karnataka and Krishnagiri in neighbouring Tamil Nadu after drinking liquor that was allegedly distributed by a political party, police said today.           
	Local people blocked the Bangalore-Chennai road for some time demanding closure of a liquor-manufacturing unit in the area and arrest of its owners.                   
	Mumbai (PTI): A Dalit farmers 17-year-old son has been selected by the US National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA) to train as an astronomer in one of the leading US universities. Sridhar Kamble, who lives in a Kolhapur village, had sent feedback on NASA scientists findings on galaxy evolution.                  
	Mumbai (PTI): The regulator directorate-general of shipping has banned foreign cargo vessels aged over 25 and gas carriers over 30 from sailing in Indian waters because of a rise in casualties during monsoon. The ban on older foreign vessels came after an analysis of accidents over the last three years showed a correlation between the age of vessels and breakdowns leading to casualties.                  
	Mumbai (PTI): Marathi playwright Vijay Tendulkar, 80, has been admitted to a Pune hospital. He is suffering from myasthenia gravis, a debilitating muscular disorder, sources said.                  
	New Delhi (PTI): A woman who has undergone miscarriages is entitled to different treatment from her employers, the Supreme Court has said. The ruling came in a case in which Punjab National Bank had terminated the services of Astamija Dash for not clearing a job confirmation test. The bank had also not given Dash, who had two miscarriages, as many opportunities to clear the test as it had given another employee.                  
	 Bhopal (PTI): A three-year-old male tiger cub was handed over to the national Van Vihar authorities by the Madhya Pradesh forest minister on Sunday.                                                                                                                         
